  "text": "TLS configuration flows from prometheus/prometheus through prometheus-common to the actual tls.Config used in HTTP clients as follows:\n\n## Configuration Definition (prometheus/prometheus)\nThe main configuration structures are defined in prometheus/config/config.go:\n- ScrapeConfig (line 747): Contains HTTPClientConfig for scrape targets\n- RemoteWriteConfig (line 1419): Contains HTTPClientConfig for remote write endpoints\n- RemoteReadConfig (line 1587): Contains HTTPClientConfig for remote read endpoints\n- AlertmanagerConfig (line 1300): Contains HTTPClientConfig for alertmanager endpoints\n- TracingConfig (line 1160): Contains TLSConfig for tracing endpoints\n\nAll these config structures embed github.com/prometheus/common/config.HTTPClientConfig or config.TLSConfig as inlined fields (e.g., line 830: `HTTPClientConfig config.HTTPClientConfig `yaml:\",inline\"`)\n\n## Configuration Validation\nConfiguration validation happens in prometheus/config/config.go during YAML parsing:\n- ScrapeConfig.UnmarshalYAML() calls HTTPClientConfig.Validate() (line 858)\n- RemoteWriteConfig.UnmarshalYAML() calls HTTPClientConfig.Validate() (line 1473)\n- RemoteReadConfig.UnmarshalYAML() calls HTTPClientConfig.Validate() (line 1628)\n- AlertmanagerConfig.UnmarshalYAML() calls HTTPClientConfig.Validate() (line 1340)\n- SetDirectory() methods propagate file path resolution to HTTPClientConfig (e.g., line 841)\n\n## TLS Application to HTTP Clients\n\n### For Scrape Targets (prometheus/scrape/scrape.go)\n- newScrapeClient() function (line 2260) receives HTTPClientConfig\n- Calls config_util.NewClientFromConfig() to create HTTP client with TLS settings applied\n- The resulting *http.Client has TLS configured via the Transport\n\n### For Remote Write/Read (prometheus/storage/remote/client.go)\n- NewWriteClient() (line 183): Calls config_util.NewClientFromConfig() with HTTPClientConfig\n- NewReadClient() (line 151): Calls config_util.NewClientFromConfig() with HTTPClientConfig\n- Both functions apply TLS configuration to the HTTP client's transport\n\n### For Alertmanagers (prometheus/notifier/alertmanagerset.go)\n- Uses config_util.NewClientFromConfig() with AlertmanagerConfig.HTTPClientConfig\n- Creates HTTP client with TLS from the configuration\n\n### For Tracing (prometheus/tracing/tracing.go)\n- buildTLSConfiguration() calls config_util.NewTLSConfig(&tracingCfg.TLSConfig) (lines 189, 222)\n- For gRPC: TLS credentials passed to otlptracegrpc.WithTLSCredentials()\n- For HTTP: TLS config passed to otlptracehttp.WithTLSClientConfig()\n\n## Service Discovery Integration\n\nService discovery configurations also support TLS:\n- HTTPClientConfig approach: discovery/http/http.go, discovery/consul/consul.go, discovery/aws/ec2.go, discovery/aws/ecs.go, discovery/digitalocean/digitalocean.go, and many others use config.NewClientFromConfig()\n- TLSConfig approach: discovery/openstack/openstack.go and discovery/triton/triton.go use config.NewTLSConfig() directly\n\nExample from discovery/openstack/openstack.go (line 197-204):\n```go\ntls, err := config.NewTLSConfig(&conf.TLSConfig)\nif err != nil {\n    return nil, err\n}\nclient.HTTPClient = http.Client{\n    Transport: &http.Transport{\n        TLSClientConfig: tls,\n        ...\n    },\n}\n```\n\n## prometheus-common (prometheus/common) Core Functions\n\nWhile prometheus-common repository is not directly cloned, the key functions it exports are:\n- config.HTTPClientConfig: Struct containing authentication, TLS, and other HTTP configuration fields\n- config.TLSConfig: Struct containing certificate files, CA files, server name, minimum TLS version, and insecure_skip_verify flag\n- config.NewClientFromConfig(cfg HTTPClientConfig, name string, opts...HTTPClientOption) (*http.Client, error): Creates a fully configured HTTP client with TLS\n- config.NewTLSConfig(cfg *TLSConfig) (*tls.Config, error): Converts TLSConfig to Go's crypto/tls.Config\n\n## YAML Configuration Flow\n\nYAML configuration files (e.g., config/testdata/conf.good.yml) define tls_config sections:\n```yaml\nscrape_configs:\n  - job_name: example\n    tls_config:\n      cert_file: /path/to/cert.pem\n      key_file: /path/to/key.pem\n      ca_file: /path/to/ca.pem\n      insecure_skip_verify: false\n      min_version: TLS12\nremote_write:\n  - url: https://remote.example.com\n    tls_config:\n      cert_file: /path/to/cert.pem\n      key_file: /path/to/key.pem\n```\n\nThese YAML sections are parsed into HTTPClientConfig/TLSConfig structs, validated, and passed to NewClientFromConfig() or NewTLSConfig() to create the actual tls.Config used by Go's net/http package."
}

